text: It's an interesting practice to use when noticing internal talk. Whenever there's internal talk and I notice it, I stop and notice what tension in the head or body has happened because of that internal talk. Then I relax and release that. And if there was an emotion with internal talk, I might find that and really like feel it fully and then kind of open to it and release it in a certain kind of way. And then that affects how strong the next talk on that topic comes, if that makes sense. That's my on-the-fly purification process. This is my last organic night here, I guess I'll say. Tomorrow night will be a closing ceremony, so I'm just reflecting on the insights I've gotten and I feel gratitude for the view.
